3.1.3 THIRD-PARTY BULK MESSAGING INTEGRATION 
The CRM system must provide seamless integration with third-party 
messaging services to allow bulk communication across multiple 
platforms through a single, user-friendly interface. The following are the 
functional requirements. 
Multi-Channel Broadcasting 
Users must be able to compose a single message and select multiple or 
all available channels (e.g., SMS, WhatsApp, Email, Slack, Telegram, 
Facebook Messenger) via an intuitive multi-select dropdown. 
Recipient Categorization 
The system must allow users to categorize and target specific groups 
such as: 
− Employers 
− Beneficiaries 
− Suppliers 
WORKCOM CONNECT – CRM REQUIREMENTS 
− Internal Staff 
Dynamic Targeting 
Recipients should be selectable based on: 
− Pre-defined groups (e.g., "All Employers", "Active Beneficiaries", 
"Registered Suppliers") 
− Filters (e.g., based on region, industry, type of pension, return 
history, payment status, branch etc.) 
Scheduling and Immediate Dispatch 
Ability to either schedule messages for future delivery or send 
immediately. 
Template Management 
Pre-approved templates for common alerts must be available, 
customizable before sending. 
Use Cases / Examples 
Employers 
− Reminders for submission of annual returns.  
− Notifications on upcoming assessment payments. 
Beneficiaries 
− Reminders to submit Life Certificates,  
− updates on pension increments or benefits changes. 
Suppliers 
− Notifications about procurement opportunities, clarifications on 
tender submissions, payment follow-ups. 
Internal Communication 
• Policy updates, internal announcements, critical alerts for staff. 
Advanced AI Usage 
• Personalization at Scale 
AI should enable dynamic personalization — inserting variables 
like Name, Employer Number, Pensioner ID into the messaging 
automatically. 
WORKCOM CONNECT – CRM REQUIREMENTS 
• Optimal Channel Prediction 
Using historical data, AI could suggest the most effective channel 
per recipient (e.g., SMS for older pensioners, Email for suppliers). 
• Smart Content Recommendations 
CRM should offer smart suggestions on message tone and 
structure based on the recipient category selected (Formal for 
suppliers, Friendly for beneficiaries). 
High level workflow 
Step 
Activity 
