4 
(Optional) Schedules message 
5 
Reviews and sends 
3.1.4 OMNICHANNEL INTERACTION VIEW 
Each customer’s communication history across all channels must be 
visible in one timeline, enabling agents to have full context of previous 
interactions regardless of the platform used. 
3.1.5 AGENT PERFORMANCE TRACKING 
Integration must allow for tracking and reporting on agent productivity 
(e.g., average handling time, resolution rates, customer satisfaction 
scores). 
3.2 CUSTOMER FEEDBACK AND SURVEYS 
The CRM must facilitate the creation, distribution, and reporting of 
surveys for employers and beneficiaries. 
An effective CRM must offer robust capabilities to collect, analyze, and 
act upon feedback from both employers and beneficiaries. This ensures 
WORKCOM CONNECT – CRM REQUIREMENTS 
that the Board continuously improves service delivery based on real, 
actionable insights from its key stakeholders. 
Requirements include: 
− Customizable surveys launched at any time. 
− Automated alerts to survey owners and participants. 
− Dynamic and visually appealing reporting post-survey. 
3.2.1 DYNAMIC AND VISUALLY APPEALING REPORTING 
After the survey period closes, the CRM must automatically generate: 
• Executive Dashboards (charts, graphs, key statistics) 
• Downloadable detailed reports (Excel, PDF) 
• Insights with AI-based analysis, such as sentiment analysis on 
free-text feedback 
3.3 COREBUSINESS SYSTEM INTEGRATION 
CRM must integrate seamlessly with the existing CoreBusiness system to 
ensure a unified, real-time, and centralized view of all critical stakeholder 
information. 
This integration is essential for streamlining Board operations, improving 
data accuracy, and enabling advanced reporting and forecasting. 
3.3.1 CENTRALIZED EMPLOYER AND BENEFICIARY PROFILES 
The CRM must pull and synchronize key data from CoreBusiness such 
as: 
− Employer registration details 
− Assessment history 
− Beneficiary payment history 
− Life certificate status 
− Employer returns submissions 
Profiles must be accessible in real-time from the CRM dashboard, with 
changes updated automatically across systems. 
Single View of Customer (SVOC) 
Ensure that a comprehensive, 360° profile is available for each 
stakeholder without toggling between systems. 
WORKCOM CONNECT – CRM REQUIREMENTS 
AI-Based Auto-Generation of Reports 
Periodic reports (e.g., monthly, quarterly) should be automatically 
generated by the system. 
Reports must include: 
− Key metrics (e.g., assessment collections, beneficiary trends 
− Recommendations generated by AI (e.g., "Focus on Region X for 
improvement in returns collection") 
− Highlight anomalies or urgent issues automatically. 
Users must also be able to request on-demand reports with custom date 
ranges and filters. 
WORKCOM CONNECT – CRM REQUIREMENTS 
4 FUTURE TRENDS AND AI ADOPTION 
To ensure that the Boards CRM module remains resilient, innovative, 
and future proof, the Board will proactively adopt emerging trends and 
intelligent technologies. 
The focus will be on building a CRM system that is not just reactive but 
predictive, not just transactional but relational, and fully aligned to 
global digital transformation standards: 
− Predictive customer insights using Machine Learning. 
− AI-powered chatbots for real-time query management. 
− Sentiment analysis from customer interactions. 
− Intelligent automation for repetitive tasks. 
− Omnichannel communication with personalized user experiences. 
INTELLIGENT AUTOMATION FOR REPETITIVE TASKS 
Automate repetitive administrative tasks such as: 
− Sending payment reminders 
Strategic Note 
By embedding AI-driven innovations early, WCFCB will not only 
enhance operational efficiency but will also position itself as a leader 
in customer-centric digital transformation within the public sector. 
WORKCOM CONNECT – CRM REQUIREMENTS 
5 CONCLUSION 
The outlined customizations and feature enhancements are designed to 
align the WorkCom Connet CRM module with the Boards strategic vision 
of a modern, intelligent, and integrated customer management system. 
By addressing key integration points such as social media aggregation, 
bulk messaging capabilities, real-time contact center linkage, and 
survey-driven feedback loops, WCFCB ensures that both employers and 
beneficiaries experience efficient, seamless, and responsive engagement. 
Incorporating emerging technologies like AI-powered automation, 
predictive analytics, sentiment analysis, and intelligent chatbots will not 
only modernize customer interactions but also position WCFCB as a 
pioneering and forward-thinking institution within the public sector. 
By embracing omnichannel communication, centralized reporting, and 
AI-driven insights, WCFCB is making a strategic investment to: 
− Strengthen stakeholder relationships, 
− Enhance operational efficiency, and 
− Future-proof its service delivery models against evolving customer 
expectations. 
Ultimately, the CRM enhancements will empower the Board to serve 
employers, beneficiaries, and stakeholders better, while positioning itself 
at the forefront of digital transformation in customer relationship 
management. 
WORKCOM CONNECT – CRM REQUIREMENTS 
